            <thetext>Normally a tooltip gets displayed 1px right and 20px below of the mouse pointer.

If a tooltip appears in an non-visible area (because the bounded widget is e.g. in the right bottom of the application) some *magic* in the popup class moves the tooltip to the visible area of the application.
However, if the moved tooltip is appearing below the mouse pointer the tooltip starts to flicker.
Explanation: the mouseover at the tooltip triggers the disappearing of the tooltip while the appear event is not executed completly by the queue.</thetext>
